@mimigstyle’s new collab with @olisohome is PERrrrrrrfection! Seriously this is my new bff bc I LOvE to iron. It was my job growing up, I hated it then, but as an adult it is so soothing. Taking time to make a fun quilt while I wait on supplies I need for a customer quilt. (Ordered the wrong thing 🫣) I love HST for their pattern versatility. I think flying geese may win for the overall design, but I’m not sure yet. That is a little too organized for me. 🤷🏼‍♀️🍾🎉 living life in the grey over here and loving it.
Always love my @havels_sewing pink cutting mat and tools. ✂️ Not shown but it was used a lot was my @olisohome iron. ❤️ always press when sewing HST.

My tree 🌲 quilt is finished. It is one of my favorites ❤️ I started with @fancythatdesignhouse FQ bundle (with panels) and @diaryofaquilter’s infamous tree block tutorial. I put my own spin on it and it was snatched right out of the dryer and used! Great flannel backing from @tashanoel1 I’ve had stashed. A perfect quilt that we all love!

An easy, no worry HST quilt for my oldest nephew. His baby brother has one with matching fabrics. I think I love the scattered randomness of what you can do with HST, they are so versatile. I love these fabric colors so much, but that is more of a coral/orange IRL than pink with the blues and greens. I can imagine this is only the beginning of the quilts I make for them ❤️ Off in the mail soon @swook4321 😘

Thank you so much to a dear friend for contacting me to make her son a T-shirt quilt. He gets the award for coolest tshirts so far in my career 😜 I backed it with a snuggly minky type which made it a beast and so heavy. I’m sure he will need that big warm quilt in New Jersey winters. Always fun to make quilts for clients but even more fun when they message me about receiving it. ❤️ thank you Denise!

Spreading Kindness, Joy, Love in my daily acts of life are my goal this year. I want to see a need and help do what I can to make someone feel seen, loved, and “worth it” - bc doesn’t that feel good when you feel that from someone else? Someone taking the time to SEE you. Love you. Send warmth to you. God gave me talents and this year my goal is to use them to be a blessing to others. Also learning to take care of myself. 🫣 When I saw a mom I follow on fb who I knew when we were younger. she has nieces my kids ages. Blah blah blah, fb stuff. Her post was to say her teenage daughter had to have bypass surgery and other very scary, complicated things. Even though her mom and family members are familiar with the medical field that is a scary situation. So I did some investigating with her grandma to get a quilt sent to her. She said she would like neutrals and texture. Sweet Allie, I pray every stitch will help remind you of how loved you are. How we are praying for you but we’ve never met IRL. When she received it after surgery her mom said she asked for the first time to have someone take her picture. And she had a smile. God using me and these scraps of fabric to bless someone who need to feel that overwhelming warmth of prayers. ❤️ Peace be with you.

Past make: the ONE and only hand stitched quilt by me with the lovely @alisonglass knit and cottons with @andoverfabrics. I used @aurifilthread I think 🤔 . This knit is just amazing in weight. It is a favorite of the kids too bc of the weight. It is a perfect bed scarf size. I always love when I see them using my quilts in their rooms. ❤️

Just a little ditty with Tula pink. She is the best there is! - sing that in your best Tom Petty voice please. Just a fun little bag, with some fun accents for texture. Anyone else like a fun project for no reason? Me too! 💕

me enamore de miami. And I need to learn Spanish ASAP and come back 🤦🏼‍♀️ I’ve never seen Miami like we have this trip. It has stolen our hearts for sure! And once I get them downloaded, I’ll show you where we went for Easter. It was a special one. Also my youngest will be 13 on the 13th and this mama…. Is in the feels. We will be back Miami!

Stephanie Kendron - southern sewist and podcaster of the #modernsewcietypodcast
